@{bg fill}                                @{fg shine}Introduction@{fg text}                                @{bg back}


          I have unlimited access to InterNet at my university,
          so I spend quite much time downloading stuff from
          AmiNet. Some days I download 4-5 MB and at that rate
          you fill a small harddisk pretty fast. So in order
          to pile up as much progs as possible on my 125 MB HD,
          I crunch all programmes with PowerPacker.
          But I've come to a point when I don't know which progs
          are crunched because there's quite a byteflow on my HD.
          So I programmed this thingy to get a report on which
          files weren't packed.

          But FilePack Informer doesn't just offer you PowerPacker
          detection. It can up to this date detect the following
          packers:

          LHA/LZH/LZX Archives
          4FE9 Linker
          CrunchMania
          Imploder
          ProPacker (RNC)
          PowerPacker
          XPK


          FilePack Informer will generate a report to the printer,
          as an ASCII-file or as an AmigaGuide. You can also
          combine these so it suites you just perfectly.



          @{" Back to Main       " link "Main" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Install " link "Install" 0}

@endnode

@node "Install" "Install"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Intro"

@{bg fill}                                  @{fg shine}Install@{fg text}                                   @{bg back}


          This one's really simple!

          Just put FilePack Informer somewhere in your path where
          you easily can find it.

          For example Sys:Tools/

          FilePack Informer can be started from CLI or by double-
          clicking on its icon.


          NOTE!
          I've included two versions of FilePack Informer since it
          requires Amos.library to run. If you have the library
          installed you can use the _nolib version. If not you will
          have to use the lib version which is bigger.
          The library is not included in this archive.



          @{" Back to Main     " link "Main" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Usage " link "Usage" 0}

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Prefs"
@prev "Install"

@{bg fill}                                   @{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}                                    @{bg back}


          In the window you will se some buttons. I will guide you
          through every one of these.

          * Select
            This allows you to choose ONE file to check.
            The result is displayed just to the right of the button.

          * About
            Tells you some inormation about FilePack Informer.

          * Quit
            I wonder what effect this one might have?

          * Preferences
            Brings up the @{" preferences " link "prefs"}-screen.

          * PreSelect Scanpaths
            Here you can @{" preselect paths " link "preselect"} that you want scanned.

          * Start Pathscan
            This will @{" start the scan " link "start"} of the preselected paths.



          @{" Back to Main           " link "Main" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Preferences " link "Prefs" 0}

@endnode

