@{bg fill}                        @{fg shine}Report Files Processed by...@{fg text}                        @{bg back}


          The seven cyclegadgets on the left side of the screen
          toggles the reportstate of a packertype.
          You can set the cyclegadgets in three positions:
          1: Report files with the packers name behind it.
          2: Report files with the filesize behind it.
          3: Don't report files.



          @{" Back to Report Settings            " link "Report" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Unpacked Files Settings " link "Unp" 0}

@endnode

@node "Unp" "Unpacked Files Settings"
@next "Output"
@prev "Files"

@{bg fill}                          @{fg shine}Unpacked Files Settings@{fg text}                           @{bg back}


          * Report All
            Tick this box if you want every single unpacked file
            reported.

          * Don't Report
            Tick this box if you don't want unpacked files reported.

          * Report Files larger than:
            Tick this one if you only want unpacked files reported
            if they are larger than a given size.
            The "reportsize" is set in the box below.

          * Report as
            This is a cyclegadget and can have two positions:
            1: Reports filesize of unpacked files.
            2: Reports unpacked files as "Not Packed".



          @{" Back to Report Settings   " link "Report" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Otput Settings " link "Output" 0}

@endnode

