@{bg fill}                               @{fg shine}Other Settings@{fg text}                               @{bg back}


          * Enter Subdirectories Recursively
            Tick this box if you want FilePack Informer to
            enter subdirectories when scanning paths.

          * Skip Icons
            Tick this one if you don't want icons to be reported.



          @{" Back to Output Settings     " link "Output" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Output Result to " link "Out" 0}

@endnode


@node "Out" "Output Result to"
@next "Dirs"
@prev "Oth"

@{bg fill}                              @{fg shine}Output Result to@{fg text}                              @{bg back}


          * Printer
            Prints a report as the paths are scanned.

          * ASCII File
            Generates a report as an ASCII-file at chosen
            destination.

          * AmigaGuide
            Tick this box if you want to have the report as an
            AmigaGuide. This is to prefer as it is very easy to
            browse afterwards.

          * ASCII Viewer
            Lets you select an ASCII-viewer to use.

          * Guide Viewer
            Lets you select a Guide-reader.



          @{" Back to Output Settings       " link "Output" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Directory Settings " link "Dirs" 0}

@endnode

@node "Dirs" "Directory Settings"
@next "PreSelect"
@prev "Prefs"

@{bg fill}                             @{fg shine}Directory Settings@{fg text}                             @{bg back}


          * Default Savedirectory for Logiles
            Lets you select a defaultdirectory for Logfiles

          * Default Savedirectory for AmigaGuides
            Lets you select a defaultdirectory for AmigaGuides

          * Default Directory for Pathlists
            Lets you select a defaultdirectory for Pathlists



          @{" Back to Preferneces Mainmenu   " link "Prefs" 0}

