@node "PreSelect" "PreSelect Scanpaths"
@next "Start"
@prev "Prefs"

@{bg fill}                            @{fg shine}PreSelect Scanpaths@{fg text}                             @{bg back}


          Here you can preselect which paths to scan later on.

          * Add Path
            Add a path to the list.
            This brings up a file-requester in which you can
            select the directory to add. If you want to cancel
            you MUST click Cancel and not press ESCape.

          * Delete
            Deletes the active path from the list.

          * Move Up/Down
            Moves the active path up or down in the list.

          * Clear All
            Clears the list. All entries are deleted from the list.

          * Load
            Load a saved Pathlist from disk.

          * Save
            Saves the Pathlist to disk.


          Click on a pathname in the list to activate it.



          @{" Back to Main              " link "Main" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Start Pathscan " link "Start" 0}

@endnode

@node "Start" "Start Pathscan"
@next "AG"
@prev "Preselect"

@{bg fill}                               @{fg shine}Start Pathscan@{fg text}                               @{bg back}


          When you start the Pathscan you will see a requester
          saying one or two of the following:
          * Ready Printer!
          * Choose Guide name
          * Choose LogFile name
          * Choose Guide and LogFile name

          You won't be able to continue until the printer is ready
          and/or you have given a name for the reports.

          Now a window will open so that you can follow what
          FilePack Informer is doing. Here you will see which
          directory is beeing scanned and which file is examined.


          When the scan is completed something like this will happen:

          If you have chosen output to AmigaGuide:
          You will see in a window how the @{" AmigaGuide report " link "AG" 0} is
          compiled.
          Aftar that you will be able to read the AmigaGuide if you
          have set the AmigaGuide-reader correctly in the
          @{" preferences " link "prefs"}.

          If you have chosen output to ASCII-file:
          You will be notified that an ASCII-file has been generated.
          You will be able to read the ASCII-file if you have set the
          ASCII-file viewer correcly in the @{" preferences " link "prefs" 0}.



          @{" Back to Main                 " link "Main" 0}

          @{" Proceed to AmigaGuide report " link "AG" 0}

@endnode

@node "AG" "AmigaGuide Report"
@next "Law"
@prev "Start"

@{bg fill}                             @{fg shine}AmigaGuide report@{fg text}                              @{bg back}


          This chapter explains how to fully understand the
          AmigaGuide report.

          When you open the AmigaGuide you will see at least three
          buttons:

          * The uppermost named "FilePacker Informer" will tell
            you some info.

          * The middle one named "Reported Files" will tell you
            which packers that are included in the report.

          Then there's on button for every preselected path.
          Click these to browse through the report.
          A file with a white comment is a packed file, and
          therefor are white reported filesizes for packed files.
          All other files (unpacked or unrecognised) have black
          comments.



          @{" Back to Start Pathscan " link "Start" 0}

          @{" Proceed to Legal       " link "Legal" 0}

@endnode

