@{bg fill}                                   @{fg shine}Legal@{fg text}                                    @{bg back}


          FilePack Informer is copyrighted which means that you can't
          claim yourself as the maker of FilePack Informer.
          You are not allowed to alter the code or this Guidedocument
          in any way.
          If you want to spread FilePack Informer you must do this as
          it is in this archive. The archive's contents is not to be
          altered in any way.

          I take no responible what FilePack Informer might do to your
          system or your HD. The damages can only be very minor since
          all temporary files are stored in a directory in RAM and
          deleted when finished. Only logfiles, Amigaguides and
          pathlists can be saved to disk.


          FilePack Informer is freeware!

          You must not make any profit in spreading this product.
          The only fee you can demand when spreading FilePack
          Informer is a nominal fee that covers diskcost and 
          postage.

          Please tell me before you include FilePack Informer in
          any collection. It would be nice to know.  ;-)
          I'll also see to that you get the latest version by
          E-mail.


          FilePack Informer is Mailware!

          This means that you must send @{" me " link "Author" 0} an E-mail or preferably
          a postcard of your town or country if you decide to keep
          FilePack Informer.
          Read the @{" Author " link "Author" 0} part to get my adress.



